variables.value: Yeah, I remember that.\nThe football and baseball clubs were butting heads over the land.
Back then, I never imagined it'd go so far\nas to split the whole town in two.
Oh right, I heard the football and baseball clubs\nclashed over the new facility.
It was supposed to be good news,\nbut it left a sour taste.
Ahh... even the parents got involved,\narguing over which club deserved the spotlight.
It became such a pointless fight.\nI really felt for the students caught in the middle.
Eh?! You think to capture me?!\nI think not!
As soon as you find that parfait place, tell me, okay?!\nI have to try it! It's my fan mission!
Eh?! You think to capture me?!\nI think not!
Dammit, what do I do now...?!
Hey Mister, don't go losin' to no Dark Society now, okay?!
We'll stay here and hold the fort.\nI'm not scared or anything... Y-You're the scared one!
Go talk to the others who stopped coming!\nWe've got to protect football in this townâ€”together!
Ugh... Are we never gonna be able to play football again...?
Be careful... The guy's an adult, you know.
Eh?! You think to capture me?!\nI think not!
Meow.\n(A lady's charm only grows when she is a purr-fectly carefree.)
Meow-yawn...\n(Not quite purr-pared to head home just yet.\nThink you understand, human?)
I don't know if I should confess to the girl I like, or...\nAh! Well, I guess it doesn't have to be today. I'll confess tomorrow.
I want to confess to her today, but my hair's kinda messy...\nMaybe tomorrow, then...
You guys picked a fight with the baseball club? That's a bold move...\nI suppose if you get cold feet, you could always try to postpone it...
One of my classmates, <FLC:KAMEO>, is always getting picked on by bullies.\nI-I hope one day I'll find the courage to help him...
<FLC:KAMEO>'s not in a club yet either...\nMaybe I'll invite him to check 'em out together.
Um... Are you really going to fight the baseball club?\nN-Not that I'm doubting you! I think you've a good shot at winning!
You're so good at dancing... unlike me.\nI'm too scared to even join one of the dance club's open rehearsals...
It's almost time for your showdown against the baseball club.\nYou might still have time to put it off, y'know... Just saying.
The football club's disbanding if it loses against West Manor, I hear.\nWell the tournament must go on... Guess training's the only option.
Wow, I never knew <FLC:YAGYU> was such a football pro!\nHe joined the club in a flash, too. I wish I could make huge decisions that easily!
Only five passed the football club's trials this time?\nYou're a lot more cut-throat than you look, huh...
Merging with Northbright and reallocating the high schoolers?\nDidn't see that one coming...\nWhatever, exams don't really start until summer anyway.
I heard you challenged Northbright's ex-manager to a match.\nGoing up against an adult like that? You're amazing. I could never...
They say a team quit the regional qualifier finals\nto go to a local festival. Choosing a festival over a tournament...?\nQuite the decision, there...
You and <FLC:SORAMIYA> were chatting up a storm at the noodle shop, huh.\nI wanna make friends with the Northbright guys, but I'm way too shy...
The football club's recruiting from the entire student body now?\nJoining a club that's made it to the national level is no small feat!
It's great you can return from the Football Gardens whenever you like.\nGives you time to catch up on stuff you've been putting off.
Here to do some last-minute preparations before the final showdown?\nI feel you. I always leave things to the last minute too.
I got texted that we should go cheer you on in the final, as a class.\nOh right! I'd better text back to say I'm totally up for it!
Eh, I'm getting stared at...\nI hope my friend gets here soon.
I'm getting stared at, again...\nI really hope my friend comes soon...
He's in the magic society, but is a bit of a bad egg.\nI bet he ran off to play with the cats on campus again...
<FLC:AYASHINO> is missing again. I can't find him anywhere.\nUh, he hasn't troubled you at all has he, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>...? Sorry!
<FLC:AYASHINO> may seem the cool, calm type, but he actually loves telling jokes.\nIt always catches the seventh graders off guard.
<FLC:AYASHINO> is really good at tricks that use misdirection and deception.\nHe cracks jokes during his tricks too. Really gets under your skin!
One word from <FLC:YAGYU>'s family can move mountains, huh?\nThe whole pitch changed, almost like magic. Couldn't believe my eyes!
<FLC:AYASHINO> turned <FLC:AKASHI>'s roses into asparagus.\nThe two have been on bad terms ever since.
We should call it a day.
It's hilly here, and jogging's a good way to lose weight, but...\nI'm sweating just from walking.
Can't believe people run up this darn hill...\nI'm sweating like a pig, and I'm just walking...
Most people that cycle to school ride electric bikes, huh.\nWith all these hills, I guess I can see why.
You were playing with that machine by the old gym storage, right?\nProbably makes for a good workout, but how does it help with football?
Is that machine by the old gym storage yours, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>?\nI didn't take you for the type to play around with that kinda stuff...
Hey, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>. Is it true that you can ride a limo to school\nwhenever you feel like it?
The other day, someone blazed past me toward the student council room.\nCould it have been... the legendary Student Council Shinobi...?
Tons of people are applying to join the football club all of a sudden.\nI'm kind of tempted too, but I'll have get in shape first.
But would I be a bother?
I heard <FLC:MOMOCHI> from the football club really knows her physical fitness.\nMaybe I could ask her to create a workout plan for me...
<FLC:MAKUSHITA>'s a big guy, but fast as heck. I guess that thing about\nsumo wrestlers being pure muscle under all their fat is true, huh...
I gave her lots of pats!
<FUL:JOSEPHINE> ran off... Heaven knows why.\nHer fancy toys at home are better than anything at that crummy park...
Therefore, I would like you to catch her for me.\nDo you have any objections?
But, having to stay\nlate sure sucks.
Now? But I'm on a diet!
You're a foodie too, eh?\nTried the Hungry <FUL:UMIBOZUMAN>burger yet? It's tastebud heaven!
You had a Hungry <FUL:UMIBOZUMAN>burger yet?\nJust one taste, and you'll become a regular!
There's a limited-edition cheese <FUL:UMIBOZUMAN>burger!\nI hope they're not sold out yet...\nWe gotta find a place to get some, ASAP!
You got the store on <MNT:NAGUMO> Street, and <FUL:TANAKA> Mart by the coast...\nYep! There isn't a single good food spot around I haven't heard of yet!
I think the quiz society's a blast. But...\nI'd guess it's not quite your cup of tea, right, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>?
Eh? You're a fan of Hungry <FUL:UMIBOZUMAN>burgers too, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>?
I kind of want to join a club, but...\nI'd have less time after classes to hunt down great new food spots.
Y'know that shopping district noodle shop? I'm kinda a regular there.\nBut lately, the guys there just can't stop going on about football!
CafÃ© Tank gives discounts to junior high schoolers.\nThe owner, <FST:MAKINO>, is so kind and generous.
Some Northbright girls asked where to get a bite in <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.\nRai Rai Noodles, that's a good suggestion, right?
I tried it yesterday!\nA juicy, succulent patty layered between tasty, soft buns...
But... I'm on a diet.\nThree's my limit! Not a single burger more!
I had one yesterday, and the day before...\nI think I'll limit myself to five, for today...
The main Hungry <FUL:UMIBOZUMAN>burger store makes the best burgers, no doubt.\nAnd the owner, Mr. <LST:SHIROTA>! He's a plump bundle of joy, so friendly!
Quiz society meets are the gym for my brain. I burn so many calories!\nI'm on a diet, but I could eat a dozen <FUL:UMIBOZUMAN>burgers and still be fine.
You're into football right, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>? Huh.\nUh, but there's nothing wrong with that! Different strokes, y'know!
You headed to the shopping district too, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>?\nWe'll hang back and chat awhile. No need to wait on us!
I was considering joining the dance club to help me get in shape.\nBut then I was like, why not just go harder in gym class?
Everywhere I go, everyone's raving about football!\nYou guys are totally trendsetters.
CafÃ© Tank's castella parfaits are to DIE for! Literally heaven\nif you have a sweet tooth.\nIt's one of those "if you know, you know" type places.
Ooh, Rai Rai's good! Mr. <LST:KIM> there's a dreamboat, they'll like him!\nHe's also a football coach, I think?
Talking back to\n<FLC:YAGYU> of all people...
The Kings are a group of guys everyone on campus looks up to.\nI only wish I could be like them...
There's this new kid who gave <FLC:YAGYU> lip.\nWe gotta get him to apologize!
Hey, you're the one who picked a fight with <FLC:YAGYU>, right?\nYou better apologize fast, or he'll make your school life a nightmare!
<FLC:SAKURAZAKI>, c'mon! It's not too late to beg <FLC:YAGYU> for forgivâ€”\nEek! Never mind, forget I said anything!
I-Is it true that <FST:RAIKA> joined the football club?\nHow'd you nab a super amazing girl like her?
<FLC:YAGYU> joined the football club?\nWonder how the baseball club will cope without their ace.
Terraforming the whole schoolyard's a bit much, don't you think?\nParents are up in arms about it. The school's in hot water now.
I was sure the Kings wouldn't just let 'em mess with the schoolyard...\nDidn't they say anything at all to you guys?
I'd die to join the Kings.\nHow d'you get in?
My dream is to become one of the Kings.\nI can't even imagine acting out against the baseball club like that...
You didn't have to go so overboard...\nThere go your chances of ever joining the Kings.
You made an enemy of the baseball club? I... I'm speechless...\n<FLC:SAKURAZAKI>, are you... actually one of the Kings...?
<FST:RAIKA>'s in my class, but I've never even spoken to her...\nMaybe you're just in a whole other league from people like us.
The football club's recruited so many big shots lately.\nAre they gearing up to take on the Kings or something?
What's the school thinking, removing the baseball faction?\nAre they insane? You don't get on the Kings' bad side...!
The baseball faction was booted out without a peep... But how?\nWho's powerful enough to pull the strings like that...?
I'm going to cram school after this.\nIt's such a hassle, though... Maybe I'll just skip.
Cram school again? This sucks.\nFailing once is no biggie, right...?
I wish my cram school teachers were as nice as <FUL:KASUMIN>...\nThey're so strict! Can't even skip class without getting an earful...
S-Sorry, did you need something?\nI have to go or I'll be late for cram school...
<FST:RAIKA>'s dance battle was so cool...\nWish I'd found something to devote myself to when I was in seventh grade.
Yeah, I don't really have book smarts...\nMaybe I'll join the football club\nand try to get scouted for a sports scholarship.
The football club must have wills of iron to train on the Hecaton.\nI'd do the same, but... Ughhh. Cram school's already such a paiiin...
You have to pass an exam to get into Southcrest High, apparently.\nI thought it was one of those easy escalator schools! This sucks...
Hey, I heard you guys made it to a super-big tournament!\nMaybe I'll give it 110% in cram school today. Why? Uh, no reason!
My rank went up a bit after the last mock exam.\nWatching you all push so hard made me realize\nI can't just stay stuck at the bottom anymore.
The football club made it all the way to the final! Right?\nI'm rooting for ya!\nCan't wait to see you guys knock the champions down a peg.
It brings me joy, seeing kids grow up healthy and happy.
Oh my, such energetic children.\nI ran like that too when I was just a nipper!
Football's popular among shopping district store owners.\nPerhaps I should give it a go, train up these old legs of mine...
I hear students practicing choir when I pass by <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> sometimes.\nSuch angelic voices. Yet for some reason, they make me feel drowsy...
I spied bulldozers chugging around <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> earlier.\nAre they building new facilities or something?
What's the latest fad taking kids by storm, "PsyRangers," is it?\nMy granddaughter's obsessed. Strikes these "transform" poses non-stop!
I love listening to the <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> wind orchestra.\nWill they cheer on the baseball club again this summer, I wonder?
I hear the <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> football team is doing quite well.\nThe whole shopping district is buzzing with talk about them.
<FST:TSUKIMI> down at the noodle shop has been in mighty fine spirits lately.\nShe says it's all due to the <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> football team doing so well!
I heard you kids made it to the tournament final.\n<FST:TSUKIMI>'s overjoyed. She feels her own training's borne fruit now too.
My hubby never helps\naround the house...
Not a single chore,\nleaves the kids to me...
He does it in his room.
I'm thinking of building a big, sprawling mall in <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.\nSay, you're middle schoolersâ€”a new hangout would be cool, right?
A new mall would be much more convenient for <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> residents.\nPlease, sign this petition, and secure a better future for our town.
Hm. Not for me it ain't.
I sooo want one of these <FST:RAIKA> portraits for myself!\nHow do you even make them?
Everyone should get to enjoy <FST:RAIKA>'s brilliance!\nThat's what he gets for trying to hog her all to himself.
<FST:RAIKA> has a lot, and I mean a LOT, of fans.\nSo just, uh... Be careful, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>.
I saw you and <FST:RAIKA> dancing on the rooftop!\nWeren't you nervous in front of so many people?
<FST:RAIKA> and <FLC:SENNO> fans are like, mortal enemies.\nMe, I think <FLC:SENNO>'s less idol-like. More, I don't know, saintly?
<FLC:SENNO> joining the football club wasn't on my bingo card, for sure...\nBut y'know, she totally has that whole "pro coordinator" vibe to her!
We came to the Civic Stadium just to see the football club in action!\nBoth <FST:RAIKA> and <FLC:SAKURAZAKI> were so cool! Cooler than cool! Ice cool!
I heard Stormridge uses some never-seen-before skills.\nThey're a historic school, and have classic vibes... I can't wait!
According to the football mag Eleven, the next match looks tough...\nHow will the two tacticians find an edge over each other?
The whole <FST:RAIKA> fan club's getting together to come cheer her on.\nBeing so devoted to someone... That must be nice.
I took it the other day. Then I mounted it, and framed it!\nTime to put it somewhere I can gaze upon her glory every day.
We <FST:RAIKA> fans are loud and proud about our love for her.\nWe're a friendly bunch, and above all, we keep things fair!
<FLC:SAKURAZAKI>, you were with <FST:RAIKA> on the rooftop, weren't you?\nDon't go making any weird passes at her now, okay?
I filmed <FST:RAIKA>'s dance battle. Front row seats an' all!\nYou're in the video too. Want me to send it to you?
<FST:RAIKA> and <FLC:SENNO> are both super beauties. But, all things considered...\n<FST:RAIKA>'s clearly number one!
Everyone's talking about the football club.\nSo <FST:RAIKA>'s popularity is gonna shoot through the roof!\nHeheh! Welcome, new devotees, to the <FST:RAIKA> fan club!
I'm still a bit of a football noob.\nBut even I can feel the hype in the air when they shoot...!\n<FST:RAIKA>'s so cool out on the pitch!
I started learning more about football after watching <FST:RAIKA> play.\nI've gotta admit, it's a blast! More fun than I expected!
It's the semifinals now. So your foes won't be pushovers, no way!\nMake sure you don't fall for their tricks. Lead <FST:RAIKA> to victory!
We're going to make signs and stuff to cheer <FST:RAIKA> on!\nWe'll have the whole of Nagasaki chanting her name!
Hey, are you interested in the Kraken?
It's the legend of the Kraken! How do you not get excited?
Oh, so you are interested in the Kraken!
You couldn't get a photo? Gah, that's unfortunate.\nIf only my back wasn't so weak!
In any case, I can't believe that it can speak...!\nThis finding will astound everyone at the next seminar!
I must make my way back to the club and prepare my presentation!\nThank you for trying! See you around.
I don't want 'em to get me!
It's the Dark Society, I tell you.
We're in a rough spot right now.
We pooled our money and bought a ball so we could play football together...\nBut that nasty Dark Society came and hid it.
Hey, the Society hasn't laid their eyes on you yet, have they?\nCan you go and look for our ball? You gotta be sneaky, though.
You're heartless...! Wait, don't tell me... You're one of them!
We're going to need your help to stand up to them. Help us find the ball they hid!
Our ball should be somewhere in South Cirrus.\nWe'll leave it to you!
We all want to become goalkeepers...\nIt's hard to practice, to be honest.
Thank you for finding our football.\nI guess it's a relief to know that the Dark Society\nwas just made up and all.
Since my friends have forgiven me,\nI'll do my best to get better,\nso we can all get back to playing football again.
I like <FUL:KASUMIN>, I really do. But she's kind of a pushover.\nMaybe I should ask another teacher about career paths...
Apparently, <FUL:KASUMIN>'s a Bigbums fan like me!\nShe doesn't look the type though.\nIt feels like I've found a kindred spirit.
Miss <LST:KASUMISAKI> hardly ever scolds us. And when she does, it rarely works.\nI guess that's what some students like, though...
I saw Miss <LST:KASUMISAKI> using the capsule machine on <MNT:NAGUMO> Street!\nSeemed to be trying to avoid attention. So keep this between us, okay?
Want to go to CafÃ© Tank?
I like snapping pics of stuff on my way home from school each day.\n'Specially the old shipyard! There's a poetic sadness to it.
One evening, I took the ropeway. Nothing compares...\nIt's like walking in the air while watching the town bathe in the sunset's glow.
I wonder if finding a four-leaf clover really brings happiness?
Oh! A four-leaf clover! For me? Thank you!
And I didn't even see it at first!\nI guess happiness was under my nose all along!
